de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.winter.model

Class RecordGroup<RecordType extends Matchable & Fusible<SchemaElementType>,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.winter.model.RecordGroup<RecordType,SchemaElementType>
  • Type Parameters:
    RecordType - 

    public class RecordGroup<RecordType extends Matchable & Fusible<SchemaElementType>,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a group of Fusibles. If the fusion process uses schema correspondences (especially in the AttributeValueFusers hasValue() method), you must extend this class and implement getSchemaCorrespondenceForRecord(record, schemaCorrespondences, schemaElement). This method must return the schema correspondence that an AttributeValueFuser should receive. To use the custom RecordGroup, create a RecordGroupFactory and set it before loading a CorrespondenceSet.
    Author:
    Oliver Lehmberg (oli@dwslab.de)
